      "content": "the firework metaphor is nice and all but i dont want to be a firework. i dont want to just burn out and flash for a second. i'm just tired of the noise and the effort. if the end result is always just emptiness, then why does the middle part have to be so exhausting? sometimes it just seems like the most logical conclusion to stop the noise and accept the quiet. it feels more honest than pretending to enjoy the struggle.",
